The paper focuses on the architecture of deep convolutional neural networks, specifically the pattern of internal skip connections used for aggregation. This topic is most closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed architecture on computational requirements and scalability, which are relevant to neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
